&gt; One thing I&#39;d suggest: remove any question(s) that you are asking, 
from the audio file. Since you&#39;re trying to study how different 
people will interpret the same file, and are trying not to give any 
hints as to what other people hear in the file, leaving the question 
in could be a factor there. For example, if you are asking a yes/no 
question in the audio, then the people listening might be inclined to 
restrict their answers to having heard a &quot;yes&quot; or a &quot;no&quot; (because the 
question implies that is what may follow). But by leaving the 
question out, you remove any hints as to what they should expect.
